Meet <b>Buddy</b>, our Citizen of the Week!<br><br>Buddy's a fun guy who really loves football. When football season's in full swing, he is either at <a href='/home/?user=funkybuddy'>24581-A Panther Road</a> in his Westridge home, or out in <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/peabody_park/">Peabody Park</a> throwing the ball around with his best friends. For over a year (he moved to Millsberry on June 23, 2006), Buddy has been scoring game-winning touchdowns, and enjoying getting to know his fellow citizens.<br><br>Since everyone knows him as a football buff, that may seem like the easiest way to start a conversation with Buddy. But if you try talking to him about music or his other interests, you'll find he has a lot to say. You might want to ask him about his house, and how he decided to build it the way he did. He's got three floors so far, and looks like he has plans for many more rooms.<br><br>His large trophy collection certainly tells a story, too. He's great at football, but also at quite a few other sports! His classmates agree that he's quite the natural athlete. Buddy loves to offer football lessons to people he meets. It's a way for him to get to know people, and find more people he can toss the ball around with! <br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Buddy, and congrats on being named Citizen of the Week!</div>
